{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017sU61nNcBEaYLmEDxYmFeN","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Session Issues Log — 2026-04-03 (Session 8)\n2\t\n3\t## Prior Sessions (Summary)\n4\t\n5\tSessions 1-6 completed all Epic 16 stories (16-1 through 16-6). Session 7 completed create-story, dev-story, and code-review for 17-1-worktree-manager. Key recurring issues:\n6\t- `_bmad/bmm/config.yaml` path incorrect (actual: `_bmad/config.yaml`)\n7\t- `codeharness coverage --min-file 80` broken due to pre-existing stats.test.ts failure\n8\t- AGENTS.md consistently missing new file entries\n9\t- Pre-existing tsc errors in unrelated files\n10\t- Proof format headers frequently wrong on first attempt (`### AC #N:` vs `## AC N:`)\n11\t\n12\t---\n13\t\n14\t### 17-1-worktree-manager — verify (2026-04-03T19:52)\n15\t\n16\t- AGENTS.md was stale (missing worktree-manager.ts entry). Fixed.\n17\t- `coverage_met` flag was false in harness state. Fixed by running `codeharness coverage --min-file 80`.\n18\t- Proof format: initial proof had `output` blocks without preceding `bash` blocks — proof parser requires `bash`+`output` pairs. Rewrote proof.\n19\t- Proof tier format: `Tier: runtime-provable` needed to be `**Tier:** runtime-provable` (bold) for tier detection regex.\n20\t- Sprint-status.yaml was reset to `backlog` by `codeharness coverage` command regenerating from sprint-state.json. Manual override to `done`.\n21\t- AC 3 runtime test used bash `time` command rather than TypeScript import. Valid but indirect evidence.\n22\t\n23\t## Token Report\n24\t- Total tool calls: 15\n25\t- By tool: Bash: 11, Read: 3, Write: 1\n26\t- Largest Bash outputs: `npm test` (~30 lines), `npx vitest run --coverage` (~30 lines)\n27\t- Files read: 3 unique, 3 total reads\n28\t- Redundant operations: coverage grep run 3 times due to output truncation\n29\t\n30\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5f276c07-4ea2-4b01-86c9-d8e4e30ebe94","uuid":"287cb0ae-9dfd-4949-adc6-030bb4b703bf","timestamp":"2026-04-03T20:01:24.502Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","content":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-04-03 (Session 8)\n\n## Prior Sessions (Summary)\n\nSessions 1-6 completed all Epic 16 stories (16-1 through 16-6). Session 7 completed create-story, dev-story, and code-review for 17-1-worktree-manager. Key recurring issues:\n- `_bmad/bmm/config.yaml` path incorrect (actual: `_bmad/config.yaml`)\n- `codeharness coverage --min-file 80` broken due to pre-existing stats.test.ts failure\n- AGENTS.md consistently missing new file entries\n- Pre-existing tsc errors in unrelated files\n- Proof format headers frequently wrong on first attempt (`### AC #N:` vs `## AC N:`)\n\n---\n\n### 17-1-worktree-manager — verify (2026-04-03T19:52)\n\n- AGENTS.md was stale (missing worktree-manager.ts entry). Fixed.\n- `coverage_met` flag was false in harness state. Fixed by running `codeharness coverage --min-file 80`.\n- Proof format: initial proof had `output` blocks without preceding `bash` blocks — proof parser requires `bash`+`output` pairs. Rewrote proof.\n- Proof tier format: `Tier: runtime-provable` needed to be `**Tier:** runtime-provable` (bold) for tier detection regex.\n- Sprint-status.yaml was reset to `backlog` by `codeharness coverage` command regenerating from sprint-state.json. Manual override to `done`.\n- AC 3 runtime test used bash `time` command rather than TypeScript import. Valid but indirect evidence.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 15\n- By tool: Bash: 11, Read: 3, Write: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: `npm test` (~30 lines), `npx vitest run --coverage` (~30 lines)\n- Files read: 3 unique, 3 total reads\n- Redundant operations: coverage grep run 3 times due to output truncation\n\n","numLines":30,"startLine":1,"totalLines":30}}}
