{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01WMYvo4tqXwwXBKhoEqxMJx","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01JNVHKofzGrfE3Jm2eZS5y3","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/17-2-lane-pool.md","old_string":"- [ ] Task 1: Create `src/lib/lane-pool.ts` with types and interfaces (AC: #1, #6, #10, #12)\n  - [ ] Define `EpicDescriptor` interface: `id: string`, `slug: string`, `stories: string[]`\n  - [ ] Define `LaneStatus` type: `'executing' | 'completed' | 'failed'`\n  - [ ] Define `Lane` interface: `epicId: string`, `laneIndex: number`, `worktreePath: string`, `status: LaneStatus`, `promise: Promise<EngineResult>`\n  - [ ] Define `LaneEvent` interface: `type: 'lane-started' | 'lane-completed' | 'lane-failed' | 'epic-queued'`, `epicId: string`, `laneIndex: number`, `timestamp: string`, `error?: string`, `result?: EngineResult`\n  - [ ] Define `PoolResult` interface: `success: boolean`, `epicsProcessed: number`, `epicResults: Map<string, EpicResult>`, `durationMs: number`\n  - [ ] Define `EpicResult` interface: `epicId: string`, `status: 'completed' | 'failed'`, `engineResult?: EngineResult`, `error?: string`, `durationMs: number`\n  - [ ] Define `ExecuteEpicFn` callback type: `(epicId: string, worktreePath: string) => Promise<EngineResult>`\n  - [ ] JSDoc all exports\n\n- [ ] Task 2: Implement `LanePool` class constructor and lane scheduling (AC: #1, #2, #5, #7)\n  - [ ] Constructor accepts `worktreeManager: WorktreeManager`, `maxParallel: number`\n  - [ ] `startPool(epics: EpicDescriptor[], executeFn: ExecuteEpicFn)` method\n  - [ ] Internal state: `activeLanes: Map<string, Lane>`, `pendingEpics: EpicDescriptor[]`, `completedEpicIds: Set<string>`\n  - [ ] Fill lanes up to `maxParallel` from the head of the pending queue\n  - [ ] Dependency check: `isEpicReady(epicIndex)` — true only if no epic with lower index is active (not in `completedEpicIds` and not failed)\n\n- [ ] Task 3: Implement the `Promise.race` scheduling loop (AC: #3, #4, #8, #9)\n  - [ ] Create a `createLane(epic)` method: calls `worktreeManager.createWorktree(epic.id, epic.slug)`, then calls `executeFn(epic.id, worktreePath)`\n  - [ ] Main loop: `while (pendingEpics.length > 0 || activeLanes.size > 0)` → fill lanes → `Promise.race` on active → process completion\n  - [ ] On lane success: add to `completedEpicIds`, record `EpicResult`, emit `lane-completed` event\n  - [ ] On lane failure: add to failed set, call `worktreeManager.cleanupWorktree(epicId)`, record `EpicResult` with error, emit `lane-failed` event\n  - [ ] After loop: return `PoolResult`\n\n- [ ] Task 4: Implement event emission (AC: #6, #10)\n  - [ ] Internal `EventEmitter` or callback array for `LaneEvent` delivery\n  - [ ] `onEvent(callback: (event: LaneEvent) => void)` method for registering listeners\n  - [ ] Emit `lane-started` when a lane is created\n  - [ ] Emit `lane-completed` when a lane's promise resolves\n  - [ ] Emit `lane-failed` when a lane's promise rejects\n  - [ ] Emit `epic-queued` when an epic enters the pending queue\n  - [ ] All events include ISO 8601 timestamp\n\n- [ ] Task 5: Handle edge cases (AC: #8, #11)\n  - [ ] Empty epics array: return immediately with empty `PoolResult`\n  - [ ] Worktree creation failure: treat as lane failure (don't crash the pool)\n  - [ ] All epics fail: pool still resolves (not rejects) with `success: false`\n  - [ ] Cleanup on pool completion: ensure no dangling promises\n\n- [ ] Task 6: Write unit tests (AC: #1-#12)\n  - [ ] Test: startPool creates up to maxParallel lanes simultaneously\n  - [ ] Test: startPool with maxParallel=2 and 4 epics — only 2 active at a time\n  - [ ] Test: each lane receives correct worktree path from WorktreeManager\n  - [ ] Test: Promise.race picks up completion and schedules next epic\n  - [ ] Test: epic independence — epic N waits for epic N-1 unless N-1 is done\