t lines 188-192 but this isn't verified by any test.\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- Remaining uncovered branches (3/34) are all unreachable defensive code paths. Not testable without artificial internal state manipulation.\n- No integration test with a real `WorktreeManager` (expected — unit tests only at this layer).\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- The candidate batching logic (lines 219-227) determines independence BEFORE adding candidates to `activeLanes`, meaning the initial batch bypasses the independence check. A comment documents this as intentional. For typical usage (maxParallel=2-3) this is fine, but with large maxParallel values it could schedule many epics concurrently that the independence model was meant to serialize.\n- `createWorktree` is synchronous (`execSync` underneath), so initial lane creation blocks the event loop. This is inherited from the `WorktreeManager` design, not a lane-pool problem.\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:**\n- None.\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total tool calls: 17\n- By tool: Bash: 8, Read: 6, Edit: 3, Grep: 1, Glob: 1, Skill: 1, Write: 0, other: 0\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): coverage run with full table (~50 lines), verbose test run (~40 lines), coverage run 2 (~30 lines)\n- Files read: 8 unique, 9 total reads (no file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: none significant — each coverage run was needed to verify incremental improvement"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a9a86b3c08677e9cd (use SendMessage with to: 'a9a86b3c08677e9cd' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 60701\ntool_uses: 31\nduration_ms: 316806</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"5f276c07-4ea2-4b01-86c9-d8e4e30ebe94","uuid":"7dbe8754-846c-4e43-baa5-35109abfd290","timestamp":"2026-04-03T20:22:20.844Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-code-review for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/17-2-lane-pool.md — perform adversarial review, fix all HIGH and MEDIUM issues found. Af